text:
two weeks ago today i kissed my kids goodbye & put my life in the hands of a higher power & a couple highly skilled surgeons. that day, i made myself & the universe a promise. if i came out alive i would accept my truths, shed my shame & own my past, no matter how uncomfortable it is. 
there are several reasons this shop means so much to me & why i place so much focus & attention on children impacted by abuse & trauma, my son being the number one reason & myself being the second. the thought of anything happening to our children is mostly likely the key architecture of hell but for some that fear is one dimensional, for me it is memories of childhood. like so so many wandering life silently suffering, i was the victim of abuse from a very early age until my teens and like most, iâ€™ve lived my life believing it was my fault & i deserved it. i have allowed the tragic perpetual anger of others be my compass and constantly measured my worth by their broken scale. i never wanted this for my kids, i did everything in my power to prevent it. someone took that away from me with my son, another broken angry person gave him the inescapable nightmares & pain that i know so well.
child abuse is something no one wants to talk about because if we donâ€™t then it just doesnâ€™t exist.  some say, â€œtheyâ€™ll grow out of it, eventually forget, right?â€ no!!, just because the abuse happens to a child and a bruise disappears, bones mend & that child eventually becomes an adult, doesnâ€™t mean the wounds are gone &  everything that happened just goes away. the emotional traumas are vast & for some, like myself, the physical repercussions of constant unrelenting abuse on the body can extend into adulthood. my surgery will not erase the years of suffering that led me there, it will not heal the many parts of myself that are still broken. what does go away and what aids in the healing process is the belief that victims arenâ€™t worthless, arenâ€™t at fault or any less deserving of love. we heal our world by not avoiding a topic because it makes some uncomfortable. we speak, & we speak loud.  so here i am, shedding my shame and showing you my scar that no child should ever grow up and own. ğŸ’•

text:
the american psychological association's hallucination-cum-epiphany that traditional masculinity is harmful to society proves that its members need their heads examined.  it's bewildering that they even contemplate, let alone express, this emotional reasoning, which runs counter to their mission of advancing psychology as a science.  i have a news flash for them: america became great thanks to traditional masculinity.  america is the home of the brave.

rather than science, the apa's twisted pronouncement reeks of sexist pathos and reflects a pessimistic political agenda.  it's just not good mental hygiene; in fact, labeling an entire group negatively is one of the cognitive distortions that cognitive behavioral therapy seeks to alleviate.  unless the apa is completely engulfed by the extremist elements of the #metoo movement subsumed by a toxic, anti-male vendetta, why would it descend into this mad morass?  it is repeating the mistakes of academia.

other cognitive distortions exhibited by the apa, such as emotional and motivated reasoning (generating arguments to corroborate a worldview), also pervade our college campuses.  the consequences are dreadful: confused and disoriented students who must tread carefully on trigger-warning eggshells scattered between safe zones.  ever vigilant lest they inadvertently offend a protected group's evolving sensibilities, many become mentally strained, even teetering on psychosis....â€
-
excerpt from americanthinker.com article 01/24/19

selection week!  also known as â€œyou canâ€™t polish a turdâ€

mind you, this is also the friend that since heâ€™s been around for a few turds of mine (and the aftermath) we have an agreement- he has to approve of someone coming into my life.

so what changed? 
it wasnâ€™t wanting something
it wasnâ€™t loa meditations
it wasnâ€™t more yoga or green juice 
healing.  getting to the root cause behind what i was hiding and pretending.  and the parade of turds disappeared. 
if i can do it.....

text:
i was 11-12 years old when r.kellyâ€™s music entered my life. i adored, admired and was a huge fan of him. i had the cds. the lyrics to every album memorized. 
in 1995 (i was 14) his album r.kelly came out (with down low) and song number 6 became me and my first boyfriends song. i can still sing every word. 
r.kelly is a musical genius with a disturbing private life. his voice was soulful, real, smooth and sexy.

text:
#thursdaythoughts ğŸ’­... with the latest annual golden globes came a new wave of support for the #metoo and timesup movement. in the past two years, a global surge of support against sexual harassment and assault has risen, sparking accusations against powerful men in a variety of industries. the revolutionary anti-sexual assault and womenâ€™s empowerment movements have opened up public conversation about womenâ€™s issues around the world. 
#metoo is about giving people a voice. the movement has encouraged numerous women to speak out about sexual violence and harassment. the #metoo website describes their motto as â€œempowerment through empathy,â€ which is a crucial message to resonate amongst survivors of abuse, to show that they are not alone. it has created a solid sisterhood, connecting strong women together, fuelling each otherâ€™s confidence. in addition to #metoo, the timesup organisation focuses on bringing safety, fairness and dignified work to working women; an endured issues that is strongly prevalent throughout many industries today. 
we do not want more, we just want equality; it sounds simple enough, but we would not have movements such as #metoo and timesup if it was that easy. 
but the creation of such movements have begun a widespread protest for change which has made an irreversible impact.  it has allowed for women to never return to the days of shame or isolation. and we believe that it is beginning to serve as a catalyst for women everywhere to stand firm in the face of adversity. 
we are living in a time where women are still fighting for basic fairness. the campaigns which we speak of encourage resilience and bravery. although it is shocking to say that in this current climate we are still fighting against issues morally incorrect, it only defines the purpose for our voices even more. ultimately, #metoo and timesup have not only added to the rights of women but have served as a safeguard for many. the unfortunate factor that we still have to battle for our safety sounds ridiculous but it is a reality that we will no longer avoid. we must continue to make it our priority to see change in equity, safety, parity and inclusion, however small it is.

text:
ğŸ“— kÃ¤rlekens antarktis (love's antarctica) by sara stridsberg (2018) ğŸ“—
.
ğŸ™ ğŸ™ ğŸ™ ğŸ™/5
.
in this book ninni, a brutally murdered woman, remember her life and murder. it is a tough life where ninni ends up using drugs, involved in prostitution and losing custody of her two children. the book is brutal and detailed in its descriptions, divided into short chapters.
stridsberg writes beautifully and creates an intense atmosphere without the story being a crime/thriller. ninni tells her story directly to you as a reader and the murderer is almost completely uninteresting. the murderer is just yet another man that hates women. one of the things that i found really haunting was the concept that you die three times: first when your heart stops beating, next when your remains are put to rest and finally the last time somebody says your name. until then you are present in the world but not able to interact with anything. considering the way society exposes murdered women this last death struck me as awful. the book made me look more closely on my love for crime in podcasts and books, i still haven't come to a conclusion so i will continue debating with myself. i also thought a lot about who gets to tell the stories of people who are at a disadvantage, how the view of women in prostitution is often simplified and used by other people to drive their own agenda. one of the best things with #metoo in sweden is that women with experience of prostitution did their own #metoo statement (the same as women of several industries like law, health care, it). now that their voices have been allowed to be heard they have raised so many important points and i'm in awe of their bravery.
.

text:
in february 2017, cnn published an investigative report entitled "sick, dying and raped in america's nursing homes". *link in bio*
.
.

this is not a new phenomenon, but one that we wanted to shed more light on given the recent case at hacienda healthcare facility in phoenix, az.  from time to time, we are going to sharing resources and tips, things to look out for, etc., for caretakers of our elderly women who - like children - are weak, vulnerable to sexual assault and unable to take care of themselves. .
.

the article begins "some of the victims can't speak. they rely on walkers and wheelchairs to leave their beds. they have been robbed of their memories. they come to nursing homes to be cared for. instead, they are sexually assaulted."
.
.

#sayhername #sayhernamenewark #elderabuse
#resist #protectourwomen #protectourgirls 
#firedup #womensrights #genderequality
#socialjustice #metoo #timesup
representing for girls and women everywhere!

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
a poem (2001) from my forthcoming memoir, "emerald rising"... photography: mair prudence 2019

journey into self

my life is a surrealistic 
matrix.
i have stumbled and fallen 
and slipped through the 
looking glass.
there is no wonderland, 
only darkness
which shrouds my existence.
as i peer through
the transparent glass curtain 
to view where i have been, 
i find 
i cannot retrogressively 
penetrate.
they don't see me. 
they don't hear me. 
i lay in shiver...
a voyeur.
life goes on as if a 
movie.
there is no escape
ultimately leaving no choice
but to 
explore.
am i to turn away from that
world?!
i hear you,  but i am 
frightened.

name: .Mair Prudence
tweet_full:
a poem (2001) from my forthcoming memoir, "emerald rising"... photography: mair prudence 2019

journey into self

my life is a surrealistic 
matrix.
i have stumbled and fallen 
and slipped through the 
looking glass.
there is no wonderland, 
only darkness
which shrouds my existence.
as i peer through
the transparent glass curtain 
to view where i have been, 
i find 
i cannot retrogressively 
penetrate.
they do not see me. 
they do not hear me. 
i lay in shiver...
a voyeur.
life goes on as if a 
movie.
there is no escape
ultimately leaving no choice
but to 
explore.
am i to turn away from that
world?!
i hear you,  but i am 
frightened.
"i know.
now..."

text:
it seems pretty fashionable lately to talk about #trauma whether or not you have it, so here are a myriad of thoughts i have on this subject. (tw: sexual violence)
â¤ï¸
1. i didnâ€™t ever receive effective help until i began trauma-informed counseling at #hopeworks of howard county, and i tried all kinds of therapists and healers before this. you do not have to be a howard county resident to receive services. cost is not a barrier here. they are mostly a center for sexual violence but they have all kinds of sister programs and legal help. call 410 997 0304 to find out more about their services or speak to someone. â¤ï¸2. there are many well-intentioned people in this world that do. not. understand. trauma. this includes friends, family, and even licensed therapists. you are not obligated to tell anyone your story. part of consent is boundary-setting with your own truth. just because someone wants to help you does not mean they have the capacity to do so. 
while the #metoo movement was #empowering and a sign that things were moving in the right direction, it has created a culture of trauma sharing as a form of social capital. â€œsafe spaceâ€ is thrown around casually. and sharing your trauma doesnâ€™t mean that you will be any more protected, or that any action will change. [throwback to the time a member of my troupe confessed their history of predatory behavior to me, threatened to rape me, and was still permitted to attend social events involving fire manipulation. the troupe was told that lies and rumors made me uncomfortable and caused me to leave voluntarily, instead of the fact that i was directly threatened and feared for the safety of my body and spirit.] â¤ï¸3. my door is not open to you, and i say this with love. i am not a trauma informed professional. if you bring me your trauma, i can relate, and i can share #hugs and tea. i can answer questions about hopeworks and give you other potential healing resources. i do not have the emotional space, training, or resources to heal you myself. this is an important distinction that is central to my own healing, and to your healing as well. 
safe journeys and much love to everyone. â¤ï¸ #consent #loveyourself #boundaries

text:
join the creatress @sunsetkava for our sexual healing support group & workshop. this workshop is for women and men who need a safe space & support to heal from their experiences with sexual abuse. we understand that it can be uncomfortable, even terrifying to face our past experiences with sexual abuse. we are here to support you through that fear, anxiety, discomfort, sadness, anger, and anything else that comes up as you take this incredibly brave step toward your healing. the deep sense of relief from release, the empowerment from your courageousness, and the love from supportive peers can bring so much hope and healing that can change our lives in beautiful ways. 
our main objective in this workshop series is to clear the energetic and psychological imprint that sexual trauma may have left on us that affects who we are and how we function in the world. it is so important and necessary that we reclaim our power over our sexuality and over our lives now and for generations to come, so that we may operate from a place of healing rather than a place of hurt. within this safe space, you will have the option to share your experiences and insights openly, write them in your journal or simply listen and work through things internally. this is a judgment-free zone, and a space full of love and healing energy. 
in session 1 we will be:
- identifying where we are now, in terms of our coping mechanisms. how have we been dealing with our pain?
- identifying new ways we can nurture ourselves and heal our pain
- gently recalling our experiences with sexual abuse
- defining "trauma" and identifying our triggers
- practicing new ways to respond to triggers
- identifying our strengths - identifying our support team
- beginning the process of "cord-cutting" (cutting energetic ties from our abuser)
- leading a group meditation
- leading a spiritual cleansing ritual

rsvp at iamthecreatress.com/ourevents (link in bio)

text:
timeâ€™s up â±
.
.
.
alicia framis â€œgender pavillionâ€, located inside sala de alcalÃ¡ 31 @culturacmadrid, addresses the role women play in our contemporary society & the rise of the fourth-wave feminism; through a series of architectural spaces, interactive installations, performances, photographs & videos.
.
.
the multidisciplinary exhibition is divided into two sections: one dedicated to pieces that are related to the architectural space and how we inhabit these rooms in an established manner. for example; one night tent (2002) a reversible fabric that transforms into a camping tent that can be used to have sexual intercourse.
.
.
.
the second one is more oriented towards social activism mostly performances that integrate fashion, design and video art with a clear political statement. for example; one of my favorite pieces is â€œmamamenâ€ (2004), a series of suits design specifically for men to carry their children to work while being able to do their daily duties. .
.
.
the costume made anti-violence clothing line is also composed by a series of gowns inscribed with black pejorative phrases used by men to discriminate women over an intense yellow fabric (frequently used to create safety vests) in order to caught the attention of the citizens when they are being attacked. the name of this clothing line â€œanti dogâ€ (2002), was inspired by a news framis heard of sexist & racist attacks made by a group of skinheads in berlin to series of immigrant women with trained dogs.
.
.
another interesting proposal is â€œ8 de junio, libran las modelosâ€ (2006), a performance where naked men are walking down the runway as a metaphor of the common abuse & exploration female models have to go through. or her latest performance â€œthe walking ceilingâ€(2018), an allegation to the social, labor, and politically discriminatory glass ceiling woman are still bearing until this day.
.
.
.
@aliciaframis discourse couldnâ€™t be more appropriate in a context like the one we are living today; when time has come for woman to raise their voices again -with movements like #metoo- to reclaim their rights to respectfully be treated as equals in a male dominated world. .
.
on view until january 27, 2019

.

 discourse couldnâ€™t be more appropriate in a context like the one we are living today; when time has come for woman to raise their voices again -with movements like  to reclaim their rights to respectfully be treated as equals in a male dominated world. .

text:
i have been serving on the board since october last year. what inspired me to serve as a board member is after spending a few years having children (my kids are now 3 and 16 months old) i decided i was ready to find a way to give back to my community, outside of my volunteering opportunities through work and church. 
i was asked by a co-worker to consider serving on the board for open arms. i felt a passion for the mission of open arms especially as the #metoo movement began to grow and issues of domestic violence and sexual assault were coming more to the forefront.

i'm not one to big myself up too much but i thought i was a very brave mama today. âœ¨
some people forget, itâ€™s not that easy to let go. i donâ€™t know if people just forget that not everyone is going to parent the same.
i know many people thatâ€™s given their baby up within weeks of them being born to family members to baby sit etc, to many that havenâ€™t and their kid is 9 already. 
who are any of us to judge!
âœ¨
as a kid, a little older than marley, i was sexually abused by a male family member till the age of 9 (that abuse only stopped, when i left jamaica to live in the uk. also keep in mind, thatâ€™s only 1 of 3+ times iâ€™ve been sexually abused but thatâ€™s for another day).
i always feared having a kid and was determined not to have one because i knew i would be overprotective like no one has ever seen before...
âœ¨
so as well having first time parents nerves, donâ€™t judge people and they way they decide to parent their own kid.
for some people like me, itâ€™s mega hard to just leave my kid with anyone. that means, even with his own grandparents.
we had a open talk today and i told them why i am the way i am and i think they understand more where i was coming from. 
slowly but surely i will start to trust those in my little circle a bit more.
but sadly itâ€™s one of the awful after affects that i have to deal with for the rest of my life. 
i may not be that mama that allows her kid to be babysit by every tom dick or harry but iâ€™m making baby steps towards the right direction.
âœ¨
 i tell my story, not so i get the glory but so that others may know hope.
i know the power of sharing a story. thatâ€™s why iâ€™ve shared mine too.
iâ€™m here to say, there is many people like me, sadly weâ€™re not the first to experience this and wonâ€™t be the last but importantly youâ€™re not alone on this journey.
when your ready to add your voice to this community, search out a few support groups, i recently have and though i havenâ€™t got too involved and comment a lot but it nice to be surround by others like myself.
âœ¨
remember itâ€™s okay to heal at your own pace ğŸ’™

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: so... i normally do not â€œtalkâ€ politics either way on fb page. however i am not shy about sharing my beliefs such as animal rights, climate control, zero waste, no plastic, being against the pipeline and the wall just to name a few. i have been labeled anywhere from an activist to a liberal yet neither are entirely true. i do not claim to be anymore that human with my own set of beliefs and values... that is why i feel very strongly to speak of this... the ruling in new york regarding late term/full term abortion makes my heart sick and my soul cry. i can not even begin to explain how much. i have always been pro choice but this crosses my moral line. as a mother who was told to choose between herself or her baby i chose my baby and we were both fine! my second child was induced neither were born under great circumstances but the circumstances donâ€™t matter the universe trusted me enough to not only bring life into this world but to protect that life with my own. it is no secret that what i believe in i am extremely passionate about... so keeping my carbon footprint small, being vegan for numerous reasons, protecting the earth and the seas, and many more all are extremely important to me, so how can i be passionate about those issues but not passionate about protecting human life? i do not believe in the death penalty because i do not think anyone has the right to determine when someone dies.... so i ask myself how is this any different? the answer for me is itâ€™s not. being an activist of sorts and seeing how big the #metoo movement got for right or wrong reasons i am not to say... that being said my heart cries out â€œif you wonâ€™t or canâ€™t i willâ€ i will take the babies left to die and i will love them no matter how long their time on earth is. if i can cry over whales, and cows, and chickens, the climate, our water supplies i can certainly cry for children sentenced to death. so i say #iwill bring them all to me, who am i to say when it is any living things time to die... it is not and if i/we canâ€™t quit playing god we are going to find ourselves living in an inhabitable environment wether there are trees, plants, bees, water or not because we become soul sick

text:
i love women. i know that they are smart, talented, capable, victors, warriors, leaders and more. i've always believed that they should be discredited with opportunities simply because they're a woman. which makes me surprised that others are surprised that women can be the perpetrators of heinous acts... just like men. i remember when north carolina first made the controversial "bathroom law" and everyone was up in arms about how men would be using it to abuse women. yet in this case, which hasn't had nearly the amount of coverage it would have if the perpetrators were men, women are the abusers. if an 18 year old boy public flaunted that he was grooming a 13 year old girl for a relationship, he'd be next in line for a "surviving..." documentary. but yet ariadna's getting paid (through her social media subscribers and continued blog coverage) and her relationship is described as "goals." i believe that if we're truly gonna "treat women as equals," the we need to call women out when they do wrong, just like we do men. there's no way these two issues would have flown under the radar if r. kelly's name or chris brown's name we're attached to them and these issues font deserve to be swept under the rug now.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
dÃ©jÃ  vu all over again? pair of vetoed #metoo proposals re-introduced in the california legislature
#
benjamin m. ebbink, of counsel with fisher phillips in sacramento (photo: courtesy photo) many legislative observers nicknamed 2018 as the â€œyear of the #metoo movement,â€ as state houses across the country (including california) introduced and enacted a wave of state laws designed to combat sexual harassment in the workplace. however, if the early weeks of this year are any indication, this trend of legislative activity will continue well into 2019 and beyond. in california, a pair of proposals that were vetoed by governor jerry brown in 2018 have already been re-introduced, illustrating that newly-sworn-in governor gavin newsom will be put to an early test on #metoo-inspired legislation. previous veto of assembly bill 3081 as introduced last year, assembly bill 3081 by assemblywoman lorena gonzalez (d-san diego) would have enacted a number of far-reaching provisions related to sexual harassment. however, by the end of the legislative process the measure had been whittled down to just two major provisions. first, the bill would have imposed joint liability on employers and labor contractors (such as temporary staffing agencies) for harassment. second, ab 3081 would have enacted new anti-retaliation protections for victims of sexual harassment, and would have created a rebuttable presumption of retaliationâ€¦

text:
a heartbreaking look at the reality of the stigma attached to alcoholics and substance abuse in our country. 
my friends won't tell their medical professionals they are addicted to alcohol and drugs because they are treated poorly when they do. 
this means they never get the right help and the stigma continues. 
the article says that in the past they needed to wait for six months sobriety for a liver transplant. there is no medical reasons for this or evidence that it's more effective. 
additionally the standard 30 days in rehab as the gold standard is also not based on facts and evidence. 
my treatment center told me the best results are seen after 90 days of treatment and a year of meetings, therapy and continued effort. most people are not staying this long and not improving in the long term. then they relapse and treatment is seen as a failure when it's not, it's being implemented incorrectly 
we are in an epidemic of substance abuse that includes alcohol yet we continue to hurt the ones suffering the most and they know it. 
we all know that everyone else loves drinking and doesn't want to stop. that's fine, no one cares about your drinking but the defensive attitudes and beliefs of alcoholism have to end of more and more of our friends, family members and children will die. 
i can't comprehend the attitude of being mean to people who are struggling with addiction.  they are in massive massive massive amounts of pain and the medical community is far behind the times. they seem to be unable to comprehend that addiction is rooted in pain and trauma and everyone deserves medical care of the highest quality, not just the rich, insured and non addicted. 
when you have alcoholism or substance abuse issues even your money can't break the stigma, it's impossible. i am well educated, professional and intelligent but when i say i am a recovering alcoholic i am immediately judged by it for the rest of my life. it's so incredibly heartbreaking ğŸ’” link in bio!

text:
when our minds go into a place of anxiety, avoidance, or urges for negative coping skills it is trying to protect us. 
chances are, your brain has been taught to not feel certain emotions and is aware of what experiences or conversations evoke those emotions. .
so it does everything it can to help you. .
today, i challenge you to say thank you, mind, for trying to protect me. .
.

text:
"one of my disappointments in the wake of the #metoo movement is the response of many good men shrinking back because of fear instead of courageously stepping forward to make a difference. the most popular quote of modern times is attributed to edmund burke, â€˜the only thing necessary for evil to triumph is for good men to do nothing.â€™ as the #metoo movement expands, the faces of men who have done great evil to women fill our news feed. what the recent gillette commercial essentially said to men, â€˜you will either be part of the problem or part of the solution.â€™ practically every woman i know who has made substantial strides toward healing from sexual abuse can identify a caring, strong and safe man in her life. restoration must include courageous fathers, brothers, husbands, counselors, pastors and bosses who value women not just in word, but in actions.
.
the general response to the #metoo movement and other cultural trends has been to champion feminism and female power. what we fail to recognize is that healthy societies and families require healthy men. i am beyond grateful for the godly men in my life! men may be part of the problem, but we must also embrace that they are a critical part of the solution. may we as women never jump on the cultural bandwagon that devalues and belittles the god-given gift of authentic manhood." - dr. juli slattery
.
read more on our blog â€œmanhood on a razorâ€™s edgeâ€.

text:
swipe left>>>>>>trigger warning for rape....
we have been reading and hearing a lot of comments about "false rape accusations" and how "the movement" has caused so many boys and men to be falsely accused of sexual assault. well here is the deal, false rape allegations pale in comparison to actual instances of rape, and most rapes go unreported. however, as a parent, the one thing that you can do to make the world a safer place for everyone is to teach your sons (and daughters) not to rape! teach them that going along with the crowd doesn't make them cool, it makes them weak. teach them that their actions can have a lifelong traumatic impact on a girl's life and saying i'm sorry after the fact won't fix it. teach them that verbal consent is a critical requirement for any physical interaction  and if it isn't 100% crystal clear that their partner has given consent, then it's a no. teach them that intoxicated partners can't consent. teach them that if you use threats, intimidation, force, or a weapon, that is rape. teach them early and often. please, teach them! because as you can see, kids can and do rape and molest other kids. and believe us when we say, "they're just kids" is no excuse! #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #mlk ğŸ“¸:pixaby

text:
the other day, i accompanied a family member to a new doctor for moral support and to serve as an additional ear. wanting to be respectful, i sat in his office listening as the doctor asked the customary questions all doctors ask. what wasnâ€™t customary was the tone he was using, the abruptness, impatience, and interrupting he did as he didnâ€™t give my family member the time to gather their thoughts so they can answer accurately giving him the whole picture of why they were there asking for his help. as is my custom, i always have a small notebook with me to jot down important recommendations a doctor gives, yet, in the first 3 minutes of me sitting there i found myself writing â€œi do not like him- he is not patient and kindâ€. it came to the point where i couldnâ€™t keep quiet anymore  and i respectfully requested that perhaps the doctor can rephrase the question he had asked and give my loved one an extra minute to answer. did i mention that through all this the patient was in so much physical pain that it was rated 10+ by them and the purpose of the visit was to have this doctor help manage and help treat their constant pain. 
i was raised to respect doctors and authority figures and value their skills and expertise. at the same time, i was encouraged to respectfully question when needed so that i can make informed decisions. there would have been a time when i was not much younger that i would sit in that office quietly feeling uncomfortable and angry and not say a thing- i would just take it because heâ€™s the doctor. today, i wonâ€™t and i canâ€™t keep quiet. 
continue in the comments below.... #empowerment #speakingup #doctors #teachersfollowteachers #parenting #struggles #pain #education #getyourhandsonot #silencednomore #metoo #wellspring

text:
@janarollerfit was sexually molested by her grandfather as a young girl. this part of her life story has had a massive impact on her life. does this resonate?
____________________________________________
when i met jana last year at the uncommon woman tour in vancouver i fell in love with her energy and her gentle soul. i always wonder how these kinds of things happen. it breaks my heart, but it also drives me deeper into my purpose to give them safe and loving platforms to be seen and heard.
____________________________________________
it has taken a lifetime of healing for jana to get to a place of loving forgiveness and peace. as she shared her story with the guests i could see the impact it had on the men and women in the audience. i could see that there were others who shared her story were holding the pain close to their hearts. janaâ€™s vulnerability and healing light gave them hope and opened them up to the grace in surrender  and the power of sharing their truth. 
____________________________________________
as women were given the mic so they could stand and share their stories and experiences with her, we could see and feel the layers of generational pain and shame begin to fall away and the healing begin. 
____________________________________________
sharing our stories saves us and saves others. i believe it with all my soul. i have witnessed it time and time again. i see it in every conversation and i saw it in every city that we stopped in during the tour. so i will continue to create these spaces for women to share, connect, heal, and be healed for as long as there are stories to share and souls to be mended. 
____________________________________________
jana is one of millions of women who have experienced sexual abuse at the hands of a loved one. in fact this kind of sexual abuse is more common than that with strangers. jana and thousands of other women are now leading the way with open conversation and their vulnerability in the hopes of igniting change, the more we educate the quicker we will eradicate the ignorance and injustices, and begin the healing process as a human collective. if you have a story you want to share, comment or dm me.

text: âœŠğŸ» me too - a #metoo experience doesn't necessarily have to mean rape. it can be your boss or a coworker making inappropriate and sexual comments that makes you feel uncomfortable. it can be a stranger (or even a friend) touching you without your consent. it can even be you, having someone over who you thought you were going to have sex with, but you backed out in the last second, and the person pushes you to go through with it. a #metoo experience can be so many things, and just because someone "tried something worse", it doesn't mean yours isn't bad too. your feelings matter. your thoughts matter. your discomfort matter. and you might be scared and don't wanna' cause' any trouble, so you just accept whatever's happening - but you shouldn't do that. speak up. tell that person they're making you uncomfortable. we need to put a stop to all of this, and we need to stand together. always âœŠğŸ» #stoprape #stopsexualharrasment #respectano #speakup #feminist #mood #bopowarrior

text:
do you compare yourself to others and feel less than? when we compare we are not being fair to ourselves. we usually take our negative believed thoughts and compare to othersâ€™ outward self - the self they want us to see and let us see - not the side of them with their limitations. in essence, we are comparing their highlight reel to our bloopers real - definitely not the same playing field! .

when you find that you are comparing yourself to others, are you able to identify what youâ€™re feeling?  you might be feeling a lacking of something. if you can identify what you feel is lacking, you will be able to recognize and prevent yourself from comparing. you are not less than.  stop putting yourself down. ğŸ’œ

text:
i didnâ€™t notice that i felt a joy for life until i lost it. now, i yearn to reclaim it but i donâ€™t know how to. rather than passing through each day on a clear cut path, i now feel like a prisoner to life. living feels like a punishment. there is immense difficulty in mustering up enough energy to get out of bed each day - and a multitude of internal questioning of why i should. i canâ€™t shake this belief that life is too tough, too meaningless, and too painful. but i know that i once felt differently. once, there was - unbeknownst to me at the time - a subtle enjoyment of the every day which i had failed to identify and appreciate. i had taken good mental health for granted as iâ€™m sure many people with that same fortune do. those that i love and those that depend on me - plus the knowledge that i was once joyful therefore can, perhaps, be so again - are what keep me in this moment from giving up. ~coping diary

~

text:
"the berliner unwille #metoo", my 10th blog post since i started my blog the inbetween album last september. i thought, for the 10th one, i'd make it special. especially, since we developed the story of our shenzhen documentary, and decided to focus on children growing up in the ever-changing city, i feel that the message in this piece really does carry something special for me. it's about me and berlin, but moreover, about how i'd like to see children, my own or not, grow up in the future. to that vision, i hope to contribute however little capacity i have, by sharing my own stories, by making documentaries, and hopefully much more. (to read the blog lost: link in profile)

special thanks to the photographer, mona singh (@monasinghphotography) as always. you rock. 
and to my writing partner ripu (@ripu.d.singh.77) who keeps encouraging me to be truer to myself as i write.

text:
#tbt to my design roots. #fanart. yup, you heard right. when i was just an awkward teen (as opposed to an awkward adult) i taught myself how to design on the computer. holla to everyone who remembers paintshop pro! yes, this graphic is like...almost 20 years old.
.

seriously, though...i had major isolation issues in high school. with a couple of major traumas under my belt by 15, combined with a less-than-ideal home-life...it could have been a recipe for disaster. and although isolation wasn't the best situation, that's where i found my groove. i spent hours writing, drawing...i learned how to design and manipulate photographs. i researched and devoured all things digital art. totally #humblebeginnings
.
.
good job, young me. you made something out of those lemons, after all â¤
.
.
.

text:
step 6 of our #16stepprogram - on how boys and men can step up and take action for #metoo.

learn to read micro-behaviours and signs of distress

in the larger context of violence against women and girls, we end up talking about issues like assault after the victim/survivor has taken the courage to share. learn to read micro-behaviours or how someoneâ€™s behaviour is changing around you. the key is to notice changes in body language, patterns like absenteeism or irregularity of any kind, physical health issues, sudden reclusiveness or anger. do not ignore these or any other signs of distress.

in collaboration with @thepixelproject
.

text:
this poetry collection was purchased from the wonderful 'poetry bookshop' in haye-on-wye (a must-visit for poetry fans). #metoo: a women's poetry anthology is not an easy-going read but a powerful and important one. emotive, potent and varied; the poets featured in this collection walk us through their many different yet similar experiences of sexual harassment, violence, assault and abuse.

i think this collection is a cathartic read for women who have gone through any of these experiences because you can see that you are not alone (which i think is one of the main motives/benefits of the #metoo movement). i would however advise against reading it if these experiences are fresh. i also think it's an important read for those who are lucky enough to have not experienced anything like the content of the collection because it will help you to understand the #metoo movement better. 
all proceeds from the sale of this collection go to women's aid so definitely one to buy! it costs Â£10 and worth every penny. ğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“šğŸ“š #amreading #bookstagram  #poetry #poetryofinstagram #poetrycommunity #metoo #hayeonwye #womensaid

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text: ğŸ–¤ i saw lots of posts regarding the #10yearschallenge and i think itâ€™s a good idea to reflect from time to time on what has happened in the last years - not in terms of appearance, but in terms of personal growth. i believe the more you grow personally, the more you can make an impact in this world. on the left side (10 years ago - recently turned 22) i donâ€™t recognize myself. i see someone who is distant from herself and her intuition, unhappy, mentally and physically unhealthy. it took a long turbulent journey to get closer to my true self and this journey isnâ€™t over. for me personally, becoming vegan was an important part of this journey. it made my body healthy and made me question my own behavior and the disastrous behavior of humans towards each other, the animals, the planet and themselves. violence and cruelty is something that i donâ€™t want to support in any way since i have experienced it myself. itâ€™s painful to admit your mistakes and take back responsibility for your life and your actions, but itâ€™s the only way to healing. itâ€™s an amazing opportunity to be the person that you want to be. i feel endless admiration for all the kind people who take on this difficult journey of self-reflection, who battle their traumas every day, who ask questions, who never let go of their empathy and sensitivity despite of all the obstacles that society puts in their way. and please donâ€™t be so hard on yourself, you are strong and inspirational! â˜€ï¸â¤ï¸#letssavetheworld #mentalhealth #empathy #bekindtoyourself #bekind #bekindtoanimals #vegan #intuition #traumahealing #stopviolence #ownyourlife #mistakesarelessons #10yearchallenge #sensitivityismysuperpower  #emotionalhealth #metoo #ptsdrecovery #depressionrecovery #selflove #selfcare #youarestrong #whatveganslooklike #nutrition #health #challengeyourfears #nobodyisperfect #cptsd

text: for the last two days i have been working on this new art piece for my big exhibition, coming up in denmark. i love how the woman is coming to life, showing me the path. for the first time in ten years, i am using acrylics - no oil so far. i must say i am totally falling in love with acrylics! i am starting out with old holland acrylic paint, because i have adored old holland oil for a very long  time. but i might just finish up with a couple of layers of oil. the lady in red will tell me. :-) i am also using amsterdam expert and other really nice brands. if you have any suggestions on a good retarder and acrylics, feel free to share. my paintings in process, however, are going to have to rest until next week. the rest of this week, i am working on my new tv project at #tv2norge and also on my public speakings for @athenas_foredrag.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
when you feel that darkness creeping over your heart take a walk.
breathe in through your lungs and imagine yourself drowning.
look through your eyes and imagine you are blind.
hear with your ear and imagine you are deaf.
feel with your hands and imagine you cannot.

no matter what it is we will have something to be blessed for. 
never forget that. (some people may have lost some of the above... it doesn't matter be grateful for what you do have)

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnnâ€™s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analyticaâ€™s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from koganâ€™s app may not have been completely deleted. koganâ€™s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaignâ€™s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of peopleâ€™s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there â€œcould have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheatingâ€. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesdayâ€™s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

- she [rebekah mercer] loved me. she was like, oh we need more of your type on our side!

your type? - the gays. she loved the gays. so did steve [bannon]. he saw us as early adopters. he figured, if you can get the gays on board, everyone else will follow. itâ€™s why he was so into the whole milo [yiannopoulos] thing.

robert mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading â€“ which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs â€“ and he listened to wylieâ€™s pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridgeâ€™s psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans.
.
- in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas itâ€™s the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
once in a lifetime you meet someone who changes the course of your life forever. i found my man. i approached mr. gerard to apologize to him after i placed myself at his studios at a protest on january 12, 2019 sponsored by the asheville survivors coalition. it didnâ€™t take me long to see something was terribly wrong with this group and as i began reading all the â€œvictimsâ€ statements, i knew this man was no #rapist or #criminal. actually, he is quite the opposite. 
when i apologized to mr. gerard, he invited me to his studio and allowed me to interview him for my #college papers. i had never been in any artists studios in my entire life. his studio is the most #magical place i have ever been. he is the most warm, loving man i have ever encountered. i completely get why women love him so much. he made me feel special, he made me feel smart and most importantly he treated me with a #respect i have never felt. that is not â€œgrooming.â€ that is a decent human who genuinely cares about other humans. he has allowed the abuse to continue locally because as a vet he believes in #freedomofspeech even if itâ€™s #defamatory. he is also one of the most #patriotic #veterans i have ever met. his life is the #immigrants #americandream. 
sadly for mr. gerard, despite the upstanding life he has lived he has became the target of a hate group that seems to have formed to terrorize him. this group actively recruits victims of domestic abuse and sexual assaults, grooms them and misplaces their anger and aggression at mr. gerard and his studios. the bigger issue is these are disgruntled employees who are forming against a former employer and terrorizing him. our local police forces and county and city leaders are letting this terror group operate in our city and now even our local #ashevilleregionalairport is being threatened openly on facebook by this group and its members. i did not believe in the #himtoo movement until now. 
mr. gerard is the face of the #himtoo movement. this kind of #activism associated with #metoo is nothing but thinly veiled #workplace #violence that needs to be stopped. #asheville and #theriverartsdistrict are not safe. #believeinmen #828isgreat #believeevidence

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

the guardian

text:
suffocation 
can suffocation work like a medicine? 
to reach out into the voids :  where breathing life isn't there
and explore and engage into conversations 
with your own thoughts - 
like those thoughts were another person and your only companion. 
those conversations neglects and wards off despair you know
what connections does your heart make? with the walls of your mind
is evolution in your reactions from panic change - 
into inquisitiveness then playfulness and later creativity 
leading you into a realm that was non existent, until -
the medicine worked its falsification on you : suffocation worked on you. 
suffocation would never walk out of your life 
unless , you realize. 
after all suffocation is just a delusion your mind temporarily created 
to protect you from harms way : so that you survive! 
poem poring out after a date with my wife in court.  thanks to indian law. 
#suffocation #poems #medicine #falsification #poetschoice #metoo #mentalharrassmentbywoman

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

mental breakdowns? disappear? or die young? why they're shielded from 'normal' people? and always have "their people" controlling access to them, their schedule and their appearances? we're a commodity! they "sell" us their lifestyle so that we'll consume all the shit they're selling! but, if you want to rise up there with them, there's a price to pay and depending how high up you progress the cost increases! we naively believed that the 'casting couch' was about the limit but turns out it's much darker than that! much, much darker! now i understand that allegations are one thing and truth is another so take people's testimonys with a pinch of salt, but, i'll say two things here, 1: american libel laws are tough, so why are the likes of tom hanks, spielberg, seth green and many others not taking their accusers to court? just hollywood? how about the music industry? wonder how good musicians never amount to much while any idiot with a vo-coder is huge? politics? is there a reason why all politicians are the same? why power corrupts? text:
ğŸƒ"i set quill to leaf. in red ink i began to write - in crooked, effortless lettering because it had been so long since i'd composed anything - the sitayana.ğŸƒ
ğŸŒ¿
read this amazing interview of the author chitra banerjee divakaruni, of the much talked about and discussed book "the forest of enchantments" in the newspaper a few days ago.
ğŸŒ·
it was amazing to know how she was inspired to write the story of the most 'victimised' character of the epic mythology "ramayana".
ğŸŒ»
the story is been narrated from sita's point of view and the author has also combined collective voices of kaikeyi, surpanakha, mandodri, and urmila among other women in the epic.
ğŸ€
sita is heard saying "yes, i'll write your stories as best as i can for without them, mine can't be complete."
ğŸ¥€
this feminist take on the most epic mythology makes this book really intriguing in my opinion.
ğŸ‚
i am yet to read any of chitra banerjee's books but this one feels like a rejenuvation for our times when we are dealing with so many gender equality issues, me too movement, and many more. i love how her characters have strong brave feminist tone to them.
ğŸŒ´
i am looking forward to reading this any time soon so as to see how sita reflects on the indifference caused to her ,respective and according to her times ,also how its comparable to today's times.
ğŸŒº
p.s :- the cover is simply so adorable. the scene belongs to a kangra school of painting from the 18th century, and shows sita embracing a large lotus leaf, her source of strength and consolation.

text:
dear joseph grant

as a child and throughout my childhood until middle school, you raped and molested me (and others). you forced your vaseline covered dick into my ass and taught me how to perform oral sex on you before i even knew what sex was. because of that i can still see the mole or whatever mark in your pubic area. i can still smell the scent of your musty balls. i still have dreams of you carrying me into your bedroom and can recall the times we were alone in the apartments on 17th and vancouver.  now, for the first time in my life i have the power, strength, and courage to let everyone know what you did to me and others around me. there is no more fear and there is no more apprehension to alert the family, city of portland, and the world of just what a monster you are. worry no more. now when i speak of this, unlike in the past, i will speak your name...gladly. when people ask me why i was suicidal i will say because my cousin joe aka j geezy of the group unlisted reality raped me...repeatedly and i didnâ€™t want to live with the pain, shame, and guilt.. when people ask why iâ€™m single, i will say because my cousin joe grant aka joe willy molested me and i donâ€™t know how to love anyone else because i can barely love myself. when people ask how i got hiv, i will let them know that my cousin joseph grant aka the cook at reoâ€™s ribs raped and molested me and i formed an unhealthy relationship with sex before i knew what sex was. my mind, body, and soul had no value and i gave it away to anyone who would take it. people can rally around you and act is if what i say is false as if you didnâ€™t go to jail for rape, thatâ€™s fine. people can rally around you and act as if you haven't physically abused the women in your life, thatâ€™s fine too. my truth is not about who believes me, itâ€™s about closure and taking ownership of a power i have never experienced because you, joseph grant. now, itâ€™s not a secret, a secret in which your power was created and thrived from.

text:
this too shall pass, queen. one day, it won't be like this. one day you won't cry for an hour at work. one day, it won't hurt as much. one day, you will feel compelled to trust and not doubt. but for now, it's okay if every now and then, you need a break and you need to go home mid day. it's okay if you have to cry for an hour in the shower to heal. it's okay to admit that sleeping feels a whole lot easier than being awake. it's okay to be tired. it's okay to feel like you're running out of patience. it's okay to feel all coping skills out! it is okay to not always be "okay." and when you're not feeling "okay," just take the day to be. be still. be present. be aware of your safe spaces and support team. be full of fresh breath; because each time you inhale, you have been blessed with another. "there's always a brighter day ahead." peace and light.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

you've forgotten about me,
but i will never forget you and that night.

i should have gotten you locked up and thrown away the key, so the only damage done would have been toÂ me.

your still out there roaming free, not a chip on your shoulder about what you've done to me.

justice won't be done.

text:
my zen place....and i need it ahead of tonight's hearing in #israel. 
the leifer extradition case continues with court hearing #45!! the defense are set to argue that leifer is mentally unfit to stand trial. 
district psychiatrist dr jacob charnes, is expected to take the stand in the jerusalem district court today. 
we are feeling very uncertain about the direction his testimony will take. 
dr charnes has overseen this case since leifer was first arrested in 2014. 
between 2014 and 2016, the district psychiatrist found leifer unfit for trial. 
in 2018 dr charnes delayed signing off new reports that stated leifer was fit for trial, wasting several court hearings and prolonging this process.
#update as soon as we hear. 
#bringleiferback -
-

malka leifer, my former school principal has been arrested in israel, but is claiming mental illness in order to avoid extradition. 
meanwhile in australia she has 74 charges of sexual assault and rape to face with numerous victims waiting for justice.
for more information visit my facebook page. dassi erlich; beyond a survivor
